inn1.comm: starts round the wicket, with a yorker outside off, and defended properly
wide outside off, Gayle lets this one go too
short and wide, and Strauss cuts, but straight to point, on a bounce
slower ball, 75mph, back of a length, outside off, and left alone
another slower ball, virtually rolls along the ground through to the keeper, it was wide and didn't involve Strauss
on target now, another cutter, and Strauss defends off the front foot
starts down the leg side, it takes Bopara's thigh, and goes for clear. But is given as wides, there was a clear noise as it passed him
length ball, just outside off, and driven to mid-off
back of a length, outside off, and Bopara lets it go through, this one carries waist high to keeper
superb shot, length ball on the off stump, and he flicks it from there, just wide of midwicket, and the timing is too goo, no power in it
pulls the length back, outside off, and Bopara defends off the back foot
short, just outside off, and Bopara pushes off the back foot, towards midwicket, and runs through for a quick single
length ball, on middle stump, angling towards off, Strauss goes back and turns it towards midwicket for one
Taylor bowls a cutter again, 7fmph, shot outside off, beats Strauss's pull and bounces twice again
bowls normal pace now, short still, and beats Strauss's pull for the pace
short and wide, normal pace, and Strauss walks towards the line of the ball, and drops it towards point and runs one
picked from in front of stumps again, just back of a length, and he turns it towards deep backward square, can't bowl middle and leg to Bopara
another slower ball, Strauss shapes for the pull and he has to wait and recover and help it towards deep fine leg
full, a hit of swing, starting middle, moving towards off, and Bopara plays it down to mid-on
angled across Strauss, and he lets this one go
Strauss looks for the pull, but perhaps it is not short enough, lucky the bottom edge doesn't go onto the stumps, will get a single
length ball, outside off, Bopara comes on to the front foot and defends

that would have been a freak dismissal, Bopara sees a ball on the leg stump, looks for an easy four, but misses, and the ball almost rolls onto the stumps off the thigh pad. Actually Rampaul is luckier here, this should have been four
back of a length, on the middle stump, and defended off the back foot
length ball, outside off, and left alone
on the middle stump, on a length, and played towards midwicket
short, outside off, played towards point
short and wide, goes back, and steers it down to third man
back of a length, turned away wristily towards midwicket, from the off stump
driven on the up, from just outside off, wide of mid-off, wide enough to get a single
finally Strauss gets the pull right, but can't beat Dwayne Bravo at square leg
tries another slower ball, on the middle stump, and easily turned away wide of square leg for two
sloppy work from Edwards at mid-off, length ball, driven on the up by Bopara, should have been one to wide of mid-off, but Edwards dives late, and lets it go through
back of a length, outside off, and pushed into the covers
lucky this time, straying down the pads, but Bopara turns it straight to square leg
back of a length, wide outside off, and he square-drives, to cover
length ball, outside off, stops a bit, and played towards cover
slower ball, misses the line, and wide down the leg side. This was bowled from at least 23 yards, from where the umpire stands
short, outside off, and helped away to third man for one
slower ball, really slow, 72mph, from 23 yards again, full, outside off, and Bopara is early into the drive, and checks it at the last moment
angled into the pads, Bopara misses out, gets one leg bye
another slower ball, Strauss has to create his own pace, and force it down to third man
another slower ball, it's short outside off, and Bopara mis-times a cut
normal pace this time, that's been his variation today, outside off, on a length, Bopara drops it towards cover, runs right away, and pulls out a dive to make the single
short, just outside off, pushed off the back foot, towards cover
length ball, just outside off, and played with a closed face, towards mid-on
wrong line again, on middle and leg, and he turns it away towards deep backwards square, Taylor does the cutting, but goes for a relay throw, and they get the third run during that throw
tries a bouncer, on the leg and middle line, beats the hook
Strauss gets the timing right this time, picks up a slower, delivery, which is wide, waits for it, and slaps it through cover
short, not always the pulling length, Strauss, though, sees it early, rocks back, and pulls it through square leg, top shot
no-ball, short, outside off, and pushed towards cover - he has been bowling from 23 yards too, this time went for less than 22
stands deep in the crease, looking for a slog perhaps, Taylor bowls a yorker, fast, 89.4mph, can't do much with it
angled into the pads, stops a bit on Bopara, instead of square leg, he goes towards midwicket, and gets one
back of a length, taken from in front of middle stump, and turned towards deep backward square leg
back to bowling the offcutter, pitches on a length, outside off, coming in, defended off the front foot
another slower ball, full, played towards mid-on, Strauss wants the single, but is sent back, would have been close had Benn collected it cleanly
short, poor bowl, and pulled away from off stump, this one sat up for him, and asked him to hit it
starts off with a yorker, angling across Strauss, he tries to run it down but misses
pitched up, wide, angling across, Strauss goes for the big drive, misses
dropped, length ball, outside off, sliced towards point, Pollard dives full length to his left, gets his hands to it but can't hold on
wide outside off, and misses out on the drive again
wide outside off, forced down to third man, Jerome Taylor is square, cuts it off well, but a slight fumble allows them to come back for two
back of a length, pitches off, angles away, defended off the back foot
back of a length, outside off, and defended off the back foot
back of a length again, Bopara looks to force it through the off side, but hits straight towards point
slower ball, fulltoss, outside off, hit straight towards cover, missed out Bopara will feel
length ball, too straight, and turned away towards square-leg boundary
length ball, on the middle stump, Strauss walks across and turns it away towards deep backward square leg
angled into the pads again, stops a touch, but he has no problem turning it around the corner for one
top shot, moves across his stumps, takes a low fulltoss, and flicks it to deep midwicket, high risk shot, but well executed
back of a length, outside off, and defended off the front foot
length ball, outside off, and driven down the ground, straight to mid-off
back of a length, outside off, and pushed off the front foot, wide of mid-off
movement, finally, starts off, and nips away, the first play and miss owing to movement
short, angling across, pulled to wide of mid-on
back of a length, angling across, and Strauss runs it down to third man
shot, it's short and wide all right, but Bopara has to thread a small gap between point and square-cover, which he does with precision
short and wide again, but this is slower, and he has to wait, still he can't go square, has to do with a single to sweeper-cover
short again, on the stumps, and turned away into the leg side for one
back of a length, angling in towards the middle stump, and helped away towards fine leg
fuller, wide, Strauss takes a step down the wicket, and drives, but can't beat point
short and wide, and Bopara punches it through the covers, it's an easy four on offer
another four, full and wide, Bopara comes right forward, drives powerfully, cover dives, gets a hand to it, but can't prevent four
fulltoss, on the off stump, played down the ground, Edwards gets a hand down to it
tries a bouncer, very short, gets it to rise head high though, Bopara tries to hook, but misses
another short ball, Bopara pulls, but is too early, and gets a bottom edge into his pads
slower ball, wide and on a length, Bopara stretches and plays it for one into the covers
length ball, on the off stump, and played straight to cover
superb shot, short and wide, but he has to wait for it, and still he can play in front of square, but he does that well, wide of sweeper-cover, gets two
length ball, on the off stump, and he drops and runs
slower ball, misdirected, down the leg side
wide outside off, length ball, Strauss drives, but is early into the shot and gets a bottom edge
over-pitched, on off stump, and driven away into the covers

he misses the 50, lack of pace does him in, it's back of a length, outside off, moving in, he is too early into his forward defensive, gets a bottom edge onto the pad, and the ball rolls through to the stumps
full and wide, driven straight to extra cover in circle
back of a length, on the stumps, and turns it around the corner
back of a length, outside off, and plays it with an open face towards point
goes wide of the crease, back of a length, angling in towards the off stump, defended off the back foot
cut away superbly, short, wide and asking for it, Prior accepts the gift even though he is new to the wicket
short and wide again, doesn't come on that well, he waits and punches it off the back foot, wide of cover
beats him outside off, from round the wicket, Strauss plays for the one angling in, this one holds its line a touch, and beats the outside edge
length ball, outside off, and drags it towards mid-on
slower ball, angling into the pads, walks across, and gets it down to fine leg
angled into the pads, and easy single for Prior
back of a length, runs it towards third man, and gets two because the fielder is placed too square
back of a length, walks across, and works it into the leg side for one
sharp, back of a length again, but on the pads, easy single for Strauss
wide again, back of a length, Prior slashes, gets a thick outside edge, down to third man
length ball, on the middle stump, Strauss goes across, and turns it into the on side
good running, back of a length, on the stumps, tucks him up, but he drops and runs, Strauss is alert too
edged wide of slip, length ball, angling across, he slashes at it and gets a thick enough edge, but they run fast, put Simmons under pressure at third man, and come back for two
angling across him, and pushed straight to cover
length ball, on the stumps, hit straight to mid-on
looks to run it down to third man, is early in the shot, gets a bottom edge, but is lucky
almost a run-out, Prior is beaten by the slower ball, it bounces in front of Ramdin, they run off the misfield, but the ball hasn't gone too far, Strauss was a goner if he had hit
full, on the stumps, turned to wide of midwicket
length ball, into the stumps, helped into the leg side
back of a length, outside off, pushed into the covers
superb fielding by Bravo at point, full and wide, driven wide of point, but Bravo dives and saves, Strauss is caught off guard, is late in running, and just makes it
thrown up, swept from outside off for one
pushed through, Strauss looks to cut, but it is too full, and he is duly beaten
Andrew Strauss reverse-sweeps! Is this Andrew Flower, the coach? from outside off, he fetches a full delivery, and beats short third man
angled into the pads, turned away to square leg
back of a length, helped away towards short third man, Sarwan is alert

too short, 80mph, on the off stump, Strauss has plenty of time to pull it to deep midwicket.
"There's been a fair amount of rubbish thrown in by WI," says Mike Atherton. "That's an underestimate," says David Gower
full, on the stumps, driven to long-on for one
full again, on the middle stump, Prior comes down to front foot, and flicks it towards short midwicket
slower ball again, outside off, and defended into covers
another slower ball, too wide, Prior waits for this for a long time, and cuts it wide of third man, Morton runs across from sweeper-cover, and dives and cuts the boundary
back of a length, outside off, and runs it down to third man
throws it up, Strauss waits for it and defends
full and flat, squeezes it under his bat

superb cricket, sees Strauss come down, fires it down the leg side, Strauss was gone for all money, no chance of getting bat to it, but he thrusts his pad onto it. Saved, he wants a single too, but the umpire is sharp in calling it a dead ball
reverse-swept from in front of leg stump, straight to short third
full, and driven to long-on
arm ball, on the stumps, played into the on side
full, on leg stump, turned towards deep midwicket
flighted, really slow, and played towards midwicket
full, on the stumps, and swept away into the gap for two
big shout for lbw, slower through the air, beats Prior on the sweep, was hitting the stump, but the point of impact was just outside off
fulltoss, and played down to long-on
full, on the stumps, and swept to deep backward square
flat, angled in, would have been wide had he not guided it to fine of fine leg, he gets three for it, and gets to his fifty
length ball, on off stump, pushed towards long-off

strange stumping, beats him with a straighter ball outside off, extra bounce, Ramdin takes a lot of time to bring it back and remove the bail, but Strauss's foot is stuck on the line, he didn't seem to know he had dragged it onto the line, good bowling to start it off though
bowls full, on the stumps, and defended back to the bowler
full again, on the stumps, and played down to long-on, easy single to get off the mark
thrown up, outside off, defended towards cover
over-pitched outside off, and driven straight to extra cover
another full ball outside off, and he drives it wristily through covers
very slow, back of a length, on the stumps, and played straight to short midwicket
short and wide, and threaded through point and short third man
full, outside off, and defended with an open face
short and wide, goes back, and cuts it to sweeper-cover
flat, wide, goes for the cut, but this is too full and fast, gets a thick edge, but it doesn't carry to short third man
paddled from in front of stumps, to fine of deep fine leg, and gets two
another premeditated paddle, it's a fulltoss, and misses out, will get only one
full, on the stumps, wristy drive to short extra
yorker, on the off stump, defended
length ball, on off stump, played for one with an open face
flighted, slow, slight turn, Shah takes a single down to long-on
flighted again, on the stumps, another single to long-on
wide of off stump, and hit to sweeper-cover
slightly short, straighter one, cut away to sweeper-cover
full, leading edge, goes to short third
deft, effective, it's a faster, fuller one, he waits for it, opens the face, and finds the gap between point and short third, the pace from Gayle does the rest
fulltoss, on the stumps, and played to long-on
wide outside off, driven along the ground to sweeper-cover, exaggerated use of bottom hand
looks to sweep, misses, gets a leg-bye
full and flat, and beats his open face
thrown up outside off, again that bottom-handed, wrsity drive, gets a thick edge to third man, short third is in the circle
thrown up on the stumps, defended back to him
slow, back of a length, and pushed down to long-on
outside off, and played with an open face
short outside off, played down to sweeper-cover
short and wide again, easy single to sweeper-cover
thrown up this time, and defended back to the bowler
another flighted delivery, on the stumps, takes a single down to long-on
thrown up outside off, driven to wide of sweeper-cover, and they run fast for two
flat and fast, 72mph, and defended towards cover
angled into the pads, turned away towards deep fine leg, they try for two, but Fidel is quick
full, on the stumps, and an easy single down to long-on
short, on off stump, played down to long-off, for want of room
full, on off stump, another trademark bottom-hand drive, all along the ground
full, on the leg stump, and an easy single to long-on
slow, on the stumps, played towards square leg
slower still, plays it this time to midwicket, dot ball
back of a length, played wide of midwicket
reverse-sweep, Gayle sees it, goes outside leg, he still fetches it, and connects properly. Morton does a good job running across from sweeper-cover, and diving to save the boundary
back of a length, on the stumps, and a single to square leg
overpitched, on the stumps, easy single down to long-on
flighted, on the pads, turned away down to fine leg
short, wide, pushed away off the back foot
flighted, on the stumps, helped away for one wide of midwicket
length ball, on off stump, and they drop and run, the off-side fielders are all on the circle
good shot, thrown up outside off, opens the face, square-drives, beats square-cover, point and sweeper-cover, top placement
short and wide, slow, and played towards sweeper-cover
short and wide again, and cut away straight to sweeper-cover
short and wide again, Shah looks to go in front of square this time, drives on the up, but Gayle is sharp at short cover
rolls his fingers around this one, on the off stump, on a length, and he defends it
back of a length, just outside off, and he can't squeeze it through the off-side field
on the pads, and an easy single this time
thrown up outside off, and driven into the covers
beats him, flatter ball this time, a hint of turn, one of the very few that have turned, surprises Ramdin too, who lets through a bye
almost played on, thrown up outside off, arm ball, Shah goes for his bottom-handed drive, gets a bottom edge
angling into the pads, and an easy single to midwicket
full, on the pads, and turned away to deep fine leg
on the pads, but can't beat short midwicket this time
back of a length, outside off, and pushed straight to point
short again, into the pads, played to square of fine leg and will come back for two easily
played straight to point, wants to test how good Benn is there. He is good enough to prevent him from going for one
fifty for Prior, this has been quite an easy innings, just like this one was, dropped it to wide of cover and came through
wide and helped away for an easy single to third man
short, on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
thrown up, on the off stump, and played towards sweeper-cover
arm ball, on the stumps, defended off the back foot
thrown up, yorker almost, Prior looks to turn it to leg, but ends up playing back to bowler
flat, on off stump, played down to long-off
arm ball again, on the off stump, played back to the bowler
mis-field at backward point ruins a pretty good over, this was a length ball, push-driven square, but Sarwan lets it go through
slower ball, on the pads, beats his attempt to play it down to fine leg
back of a length, into the pads, one to deep fine leg
poor work from Been, played with an open face towards point, Benn takes a step in, but doesn't bend low enough. Why is this giant fielding at point anyway
angled into the pads, turned down to fine leg for the 200th run of the innings
length ball, on the ground, driven down to long-on
back of a length, on the off stump, comes on too slowly, defended back to the bowler
fine-leg is up, starts off with a yorker-gone-wrong on the leg stump, beats fine leg, but the deep backward square keeps them down to two
fulltoss, the bottom hand comes off, and he gets a single to wide of long-on
fulltoss, outside leg, wide
length ball, on the stumps, Sarwan at midwicket does well to dive and save four
Sarwan can't stop this one, bowls short with a field-set for full and straight bowling, Shah smashes it across the line, Sarwan dives from midwicket, gets a hand to it, but it still goes for four
super shot, in-swinging, full, Shah presents the full face of the bat, times it superbly, finds the gap between mid-on and extra cover, no followthrough
finally gets the yorker right, dug out, and played towards point
slower ball, and way down the leg side
slower ball, Prior steps out, waits for the offcutter, goes through with his shot, straight and in the air, well connected, hits the ropes on half-volley
angling into the stumps, and chipped away to wide of midwicket
looks to make room (all deep fielders are in the on side), it's short and on the stumps, but can't free his arms, played back to the bowler
slower off cutter again, slogged away towards midwicket, can't get the gap between deep midwicket and long-on
another slower ball, on the pads, nurdled into the leg side for one
on the stumps, pushes on the run, deliberately doesn't hit it powerfully, by the time Bravo comes in from deep midwicket, they run two
half-volley outside off, driven with open face towards sweeper-cover
slower ball again, hit hard but straight to mid-off
low fulltoss, on the stumps, played into the on side for one
that has to be a >b>drop, Shah drags it from outside, almost a top-spin forehand, Sammy at deep midwicket runs it, and finds out he has been lobbed. First six of the innings, fifty for Shah
back of a length, played towards point
shot, that's the T20 spirit, goes outside off, gets on a knee, and scoops it over short fine
angling into the pads, a single to short fine leg
full, on the off stump, and driven wide of mid-on for two
short and wide, with a leg-side field, Prior doesn't let temptation come in the way of connecting this, clearing cover easily and calmly
yorker, on the leg stump, dug out to maybe three feet from the stumps, and they go through for one
slower ball, fulltoss on the pads, easy two between long-on and deep midwicket
over-pitched, outside off, played down the ground, long-on is back
arm ball, on the stumps, looks to go extra cover, but there is no spin and is cramped, gets a single to cover though
flatter, on the stumps, played down to mid-off
lofted down the ground, straight, too straight for long-on, but Sammy does a good job, putting in the dive
full, on the stumps, played down to long-off
slow, very slow, thrown higher too, Prior misses the slog sweep, but gets a leg-bye
full, outside off, and a single down to long-off
full, on the stumps, played back to the bowler
length ball, outside off, drives, get a thick edge towards third man
makes room, bowler goes wide, prior stretches, but he is too far to make proper contact
length ball, outside off, played with soft hands, wide of long-off, gets two
slower ball, outside off, and he gets a single to sweeper-cover
looks to make room, Pollard follows him this time, gets a single down to long-on
back of a length, adding into the pads, and they rush through for one to square leg
length ball, on leg stump, played down the ground for one
slower ball, back off a length, but into the pads, the offcut beats the bat, but he gets four leg-byes
full, on the pads, played to wide of long-on for two
no-ball, free-hit time, full, angling in, and they get a tight single to square leg
length ball, outside off, Shah stands tall, drags it from outside off, and lofts it over cow's corner

slog-sweep off a fast bowler, and he doesn't quite get enough on it, it was wide outside off, so he had to drag it, and perhaps that's why didn't get enough to clear deep midwicket. There was a century in sight, but well played Owais
length ball, slow, steps down to play it to long-off

gone first ball, carries with him the IPL golden-duck flu, length ball, on off stump, is way too early into the shot, and an easy catch for Pollard, maybe he was surprised by the slowness of the pitch, but after 40 overs of watching should have known better
and plays a knee-high fulltoss into the on side for an easy single
steps out, Pollard bowls the offcutter, and follows him too
angled into the pads, played to just wide of short fine leg
shapes for the scoop, Pollard bowls short and wide, he still gets enough bat to clear short fine leg
length ball, outside off, scoop shot again, clears short fine, but hasn't connected well enough for four
back of a length, outside, played to wide of mid-off
Prior slogs, misses, and Taylor hits. Simple dismissal. Full and straight, and another England batsman misses out on a hundred. In fact he gets out on the Aussie devil's number
slower ball, offcutter, across him, plays down to third man
full, outside off, inside edge, onto the pad, no run
back of a length, turned towards square leg, a fumble from Bravo turns a tight single into an easy one
looks to make room, Pollard follows him, can't get the big shot
steps out, gets enough bat to clear the in-field, and also finds the gap between long-on and midwicket
steps out again, gets a low fulltoss, turns it straight towards midwicket
Morgan dances down too, bowls the slower offcutter, he runs it down to third man for one
steps out and drives powerfully down to long-off, and they take two having hit it straight to Benn
shapes up for a scoop, but tries a reverse-sweep, but this is full and straight delivery, he can get only one to point
300 up, with an easy pull off a short delivery, places it perfectly with deep backward square and midwicket
short again, Collingwood pulls off the front foot, but gets the sweet part of the bat, clears the longest part of the field, square leg
full and wide, Collingwood slogs, and misses
finally Taylor goes full and straight, Collingwood makes room, tries a hard hit, misses, the leg stump is out of the ground. Makes you wonder why he has been trying those limp bouncers
good yorker first up, although he is making room, he can't get a run off it
back of a length, outside off, takes a single to third man
and Pollard starts off with a fulltoss on the pads, fine leg inside the circle, Bresnan doesn't look the gift horse in the mouth and gets four
length ball, outside off, flashes and misses
another fulltoss, lofts it towards deep midwicket, Chanderpaul is not all the way back to the boundary, and is lobbed by this one
back of a length, on the stumps, and played back to the bowler
slower ball, Bresnan is early into this lofted shot, and holes out to long-on, the offcutter does the trick
length ball, on the stumps, walks across and hits it to wide of deep midwicket, gets two
full and straight, plays towards extra cover, gets one, brings Morgan on strike
tries the scoop, Taylor bowls the slower ball, offcutter, ends up playing it into his chin, gets one for it
back of a length, outside leg, fine leg is up, gets enough bat for it to run for three
full and straight, can't get under it, just one to long-off
slower bouncer, totally deceives Broad, who finally tries to upper-cut, but is early into it
no I was wrong this is a wide, bowled from 23 yards again, slower one, but much too wide of off stump
the legal last ball, slower again, chipped over extra cover, will get two to sweeper-cover

inn2.comm: starts off, moving away, Gayle shoulders arms
short and wide, left alone
length ball, angling across, and Gayle lets this one go too
pitches it up, invites a drive, gets it, but Gayle gets an inside edge onto the pads
spanked, just back of a length, angling across, just enough width for him, it races through the covers
full, angling away, Gayle goes for the big booming drive, misses completely
angled into the pads, Morton misses on the flick, no signal on what I thought was a leg-bye
short and angling across, cut away to wide of mid-off
back of a length, on the stumps, drops it down towards cover, and rushes through for one
short, on the stumps, and punched off the back foot, straight to mid-off
misses out on this one, this was a leg-stump half-volley, all he manages is a thick inside edge onto the pads
digs it in short, no room, stands tall, and plays it back to the bowler
spanks it through off side again, just back of a length, slight width, and punches it through extra cover
and Broad tries to follow the leg slip, bowls it down the leg side
soft, really soft, he has been waiting for anything short, but this one is on the stumps, he goes for the pull, hits him high on the bat, and a dolly offered to Bopara at mid-on
short, into the body, and pulled away easily to fine-leg, and there isn't one
leg-stump half-volley, and all it needed was a tickle, Sarwan gives it more than that, and gets four more
back of a length, outside off, Sarwan goes for the cut, and misses
that's a good short delivery, on the off-stump line, not easy to pull, no room to cut, he plays it on almost, but gets a single towards square leg
lovely catch from Strauss, length ball, outside off, Sarwan goes for the drive, stops a bit, flying to the left of cover, and Strauss sticks out his left hand, and takes it cleanly
full, on the pad, played to wide of midwicket for one
back of a length, on off stump, and punched crisply off the back foot, straight towards mid-off
length ball, outside off, there for the drive, and he drives it straight towards point
goes back of a length again, no room, and he pushes it from the back foot, towards mid-off again
again tucks him up, again no room, and again he plays it to mid-off
full ball, angling in, Chanderpaul shuffles towards it, the two meet at a suitable location in front of the stumps, and he turns it around to square of fine leg
starts outside off, Chanderpaul shuffles and pokes at it, the ball holds its line a touch, and beats him, well bowled
he has found the gap perfectly, outside off, length ball, gets the edge, but the slip is wide, very wide, almost fourth slip, and he gets four
full, outside off, angling in, defended off the front foot
slower ball, on the stumps, defended off the front foot, into the on side
short and wide, Shiv looks to cut, this one doesn't come on too fast, and he ends up playing it back to the bowler
full and wide, he flashes, hard, gets a thick edge, square of third man, gets two
length ball, outside off, drives, gets an inside edge, onto his front pad
another length ball, outside off, driven crisply, but straight to mid-off
back of a length, goes back, and pushes it to wide of mid-on
shot, he has almost manufactured that, short angling towards off stump, shuffles across, makes it into leg-stump line, and pulls fine of square leg and square of fine leg

has he dropped it?, full, on the pads, Shiv shuffles too far, seems to have got a tickle, there is a noise, Prior dives to his right, gets a hand to it, but can't collect it cleanly. Sorry Matt, you didn't drop it, it came off the pad
angled into the pads, turned around the corner for one
good shot, wide outside off, gets his front foot, and pushes it through the cover field, not a full-blooded drive
full, outside off, almost a yorker, played down towards mid-off
length ball, angling in towards the stumps, played straight to mid-off
back of a length, cramps him up with the angle, and is played back to the bowler
full and wide, Shiv moves across, drives but straight to mid-off
half-volley on off stump, driven powerfully, but straight to mid-on
that's squeezed through, pulls the length back, Morton moves half forward and pokes at it, the angle gets the inside edge, but it misses the leg stump
slower ball, deceives Shiv, and he has a fielder in place, but this one doesn't carry to short midwicket
fuller, normal pace, half-volley, and Shiv drives on the run, perfect placement, between mid-off and extra cover
length ball, middle and angling away, Shiv angles across, flicks it wide of midwicket
another length ball, on the stumps, he walks across and flicks again, but this time straight to square leg
into the pads, just back of a length, played square of the leg gully
length ball, angling in towards off stump, defended back towards Broad
slower ball, played towards cover, Morton surprisingly wants one, Shiv rightly sends him back, and a dive gets him in
on target, angling in towards the off stump, played back to Broad
back of a length, holding its line this time, played with an open face, towards the fourth slip
beats him outside off again, this one holds its line again, and Shiv plays inside the line
nips back, from outside off, beats him, but can't get the lbw because it is too high and going down
pitches it up this time, on the leg stump, Morton flicks extravagantly, finds the gap between short fine and keeper
back of a length, outside off, and punched towards cover
short, into the body, pulled away all along the ground towards deep backward square
slower ball, on the stumps, and turned away to fine leg, which is pretty square

two shouts in one, he gets it to nip back from outside off, would have hit the stumps, but Morton has come forward and perhaps outside the line of off, the ball lobs off towards slip where Swann takes a diving catch, but there is no edge
beats him outside again, again didn't come in with angle, again Shiv shuffles across, and plays inside the line
beats him with a quick one this time, sharp at 86mph, angling in this time, he looks to cut, but plays over it
full, on the middle stump, driven to mid-on
full, just outside off, and played with an open face into the covers
slower cutter, 74mph, he goes across towards off stump, and defends it towards cover
full, on the stumps, this time he has moved across enough to help it onto the leg side for one
slower ball, fulltoss it is, and he plays towards point, where Morgan makes a good diving save
back of a length, angling across, defended towards cover
length ball, played off the front foot, back to the bowler
fuller, on the stumps, defended with soft hands
back of a length, on the pads, and he helps himself to a single to deep backward square
angled into the pads, and he gets a one to deep backward square
back of a length, into the stumps, played towards square leg for one
short, angling across, cut but doesn't time well, goes straight to Collingwood, who is back at backward point
length ball, played down to mid-off where Swann mis-fields and allows a single
just back of a length, run down towards third man
short, no room, and cut straight towards point
back of a length, just outside off, played back to the bowler
back of a length, pushed straight to cover
back of a length, pushed through to cover
back of a length again, outside off, played with an open face towards point
wide outside off, looks for the big cut, and he misses it
big shout from Prior, mostly because he has taken a clean one diving forward, Bresnan, who beaten Morton with a slower one, is not interested. No surprises too - there is no edge
length ball, angling into the pads, played to mid-on
length ball, on off stump, played towards midwicket
back of a length, outside off, played with an open face
back of a length, outside off, driven off the back foot, to cover
straighter, but keeps it back of a length, and Morton's weight is forward, he ends up playing it back to the bowler
slight mis-hit but the idea is right, length ball, goes down the ground, gets the inside half of the bat, but just about clears midwicket
length ball, on the off stump, and defended off the back foot
back of a length, angling in, Shiv gets across, and helps it down to fine leg

and Morton is run out again! The Shiv and Runako band has given us another symphony. He had punched this powerfully off the back foot, wide of sweeper-cover, he wants two, Shiv never wanted it, the hand is up immediately, but Morton keeps running, maybe not expecting the throw to come his end, but Collingwood goes non-striker's end, on the top of stumps, and finds Morton short
length ball, on the stumps, and defended back to the bowler
length ball, angling in, and he drops into the on side and runs
pitched on a length, outside off, and played with an open face towards point
pitched up, outside off, and driven straight to mid-off
angled across him, full, driven to cover
back of a length, slower ball, on leg stump, beats him with the lack of pace
same length, but goes across him this time, defended off back foot
back of a length, angling across, and pushed down to long-off
length ball, just outside off, played watchfully towards mid-off
back of a length, turns it towards square leg
wide outside off, length ball too, times to drive well, but one-bounce to cover
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, and defended into the covers
back of a length, outside off, and played towards point
no width again, full, on off stump, played to mid-off
length ball, on off, this time he walks across, and plays it towards deep backward square

close shout, Bravo has come across, is beaten by the slower offcutter, but Steve David reckons this might be going down the leg side. No problems with height, though. Hawkeye says, kissing the outside part of leg stump. Fair call, ump
length ball, on leg stump, played straight to midwicket
short, angling across, and cut towards sweeper-cover
back of a length, Bravo looks to walk down, the ball gets a bit big on him, and it is played towards midwicket
typical Bravo shot, a sort of flick down the ground, extravagant followthrough, one for the photographers, gets six too, over long-on
lovely shot, even better, back of a length, onto the pads, just a clip, and it flies along the ground (pardon the expression) towards the midwicket boundary, superb timing
full, on the stumps, drives it down to long-on for one
length ball, outside off, defends off the front foot
slower ball, over-pitched, outside off, and driven with an open face towards third man
yorker, outside off, and defended towards cover
slower cutter, just back of a length, around off stump, plays it back to the bowler
full, on middle stump, played straight to midwicket, with that Shiv's strike-rate hits 50, exactly
length ball, accurate again, no room, and he plays it back to the bowler
good timing again, poor delivery for a change, fullish, onto the pads, flicked away, fine of deep fine leg
back of a length, goes for the cut, but it's too close to him and he gets beaten
length ball, middle stump, played straight to midwicket
another Bravo special, where are the lensman? length ball, slower too, picks it up early, smooth flow, lofts over long-on, holds the pose
gets straighter this time, no room, played to cover
angled into the pads, flicked away to midwicket for one
flights it up, did I see some drift away from Bravo, too full anyway, played back to the bowler
lovely bowling, would have got a wicket for that had Prior not missed it by six feet, flighted, dipping, drawing Bravo out, beating him with the break, familiar scenes behind the wicket
plays this one as if nothing happened previous ball, good-looking cover-drive, against the spin, and gets two to wide of sweeper-cover
full, on middle stump, flicked straight down the ground
full, angling in, from round the wicket, played to midwicket
turn there, slow albeit, pitches leg, from round the stumps, and then turns away and ends off stump, defended back to the bowler
starts with a wide from pavilion End, down the leg side

and gets Bravo with the second, big big wicket. Back of a length, jagging in from outside off, Bravo steps across, misses, is hit in front of middle and leg (more leg than middle), is given, seeming to go down the leg side
length ball, wide outside off, and is cut furiously into the ground, and straight to point
wide outside off, gets a thick edge, and their 100th run, not at the pace they would have liked
overpitched outside off, driven straight to cover
slower ball, full, almost a yorker, a single to cover-point
back of a length, angling into the stumps, and turned around the corner for one
full, some drift there, driven with an open face, beats point, and gets two before sweeper-cover can get around
superb bowling, straighter one this time, just back of a length, outside off, Ramdin looks to cut, but ends up playing inside the line
defended off the front foot, gets a thick outside edge
driven against the spin, but straight to cover
loopier this time, makes him wait, and it turns slowly, he defends
full, outside off, driven for one to sweeper-cover
slower ball, loopy too, outside off, and played towards point
back of a length, angling into the pads, and gets a leg-bye there
good rive, over-pitched outside off, hit to the left of sweeper-cover, and he gets two
slower ball, on the stumps, played down to mid-on
length ball, outside off, gets a single in the covers
back of a length, runs it down to third man
floater, on the stumps, defended off the back foot
flighted outside off, Ramdin looks to cut it, it's way too full for that, gets a big bottom edge but doesn't play it on
this one stays low, and is in front of stumps too, does well to get bat down in time
thrown up on the off stump, played back to the bowler
back of a length, on the stumps, pushed down to long-on
flighted generously, gets too close to Ramdin who drives it well, to the right of sweeper-cover, but Anderson puts out a full-length dive to save four
slower ball, outside off, and hit to sweeper-cover
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, defended off back foot
back of a length again, outside off, he opens his face on it and gets one to third man
beats him outside off, much like Broad did earlier, Chanderpaul plays for the angling-in delivery, this one holds its line, and he ends up playing inside the line
back of a length, outside off, played with an open face towards point
length delivery, on the stumps, and turned away towards square leg for one
flighted outside off, driven down the ground
floated outside off, driven but straight to cover
length ball, outside off, chopped towards third man
angling in with the arm, and he plays it towards square leg
smart bowling, but Ramdin gets a four, faster flatter, straighter one, Ramdin goes for his shot, gets a thick edge, aerial, Shah dives at short third man, but can't get there
thrown up on the stumps, pushed to midwicket
length ball, on the pads, and played away towards fine leg
back of a length, on middle stump, pushed down to mid-on
pitched up, Chanderpaul looks to drive into the leg side, gets an inside edge onto the pad
leg-side half-volley, played towards deep backward square
back of a length, on the stumps, pushed down to long-on
overpitched, on the leg stump, a single into the leg side
thrown up, on off stump, played with an open face for one
goes inside-out, full ball, over extra cover, gets two
well-flighted, on off stump, driven back to the bowler
just outside off, plays it with an open face and gets one
angling into the pads, gets one to deep square leg
beats him with the drifter, outside off, Ramdin looks to drive, but plays inside the line
back of a length, opens the face, gets a single to cover
length ball, on the stumps, played back to the bowler
overpitched, on the leg stump, gets one to long-on
back of a length, pretty straight, defended off the back foot
length ball, on the stumps, and played to the left of Collingwood, who does well
on the pads, gets a single into the leg side
full, outside off, and played straight to cover
angled down the leg side, and gets one to the left of short fine
thrown up, on the pads, and gets a one to long-on
flights it, angles it into the pads, and he gets one to long-on
quick hands from Ramdin, quicker ball, just outside off, and he goes back fast to cut it through point for two
thrown up, on the pads, looks for one down the ground, Collingwood dives from midwicket to prevent the one
back of a length, across him, and he plays it back to Collingwood
thrown up this time, played down to long-off for one
back of a length, on the middle stump, played down to long-on
full, on the pads, but can't beat midwicket
on the pads again, gets one to fine leg
yorker, on off stump, dug out, but no run
back of a length, around the off-stump line, played towards midwicket
short and wide, stays low, and all he can do is play it back to the bowler
length ball, around off again, and defended back to bowler
back of a length, looks to hit it down the ground, but can't beat the bowler
short and wide, cut limply for one to cover
somebody looks to break the shackles, length ball, walks across the line, and scoops it over Prior's head, the fine leg is wide enough for him to get four
length ball, on the pads, and played down to fine leg, gets to fifty, a bizarre little innings, coming in 96 balls, chasing 329
almost holes out, short, into the pads, is early into the flick, but the ball doesn't carry to deep backward square
full, on off, played towards cover, no run
and he shows intent upon reaching his fifty, length ball, on pads, and chips it over midwicket
and more intent, full ball, lofts it over midwicket, gets more power into this one
length ball, outside off, runs it down to third man
goes for the scoop, but the fine leg is back, gets only two
goes for the pull, but it is too full, and he ends up playing it back to bowler
fuller, on the off stump, plays it down to long-off
slogs this time, from the pads, and gets two to the left of deep square leg
back-of-the-hand slower ball, way too short, though, Ramdin hits it straight towards sweeper-cover
short, there for the pull, he does that but doesn't get enough power into it, gets two to deep midwicket
slower ball outside off, gets an inside edge past Prior
length ball, on the pads, gets one to long-on
back of a length, on the pads, pulls it straight to short fine
offcutter, driven to wide of cover for one
goes for the big slog, gets an outside edge, the ball skies and falls safe between long-off and extra-cover
short, as expected, plays limply towards cover for one
short, into the body, pulled away to the left of deep backward square and gets two
another short delivery, not much pace on it, and Shiv pulls it to wide of mid-on for four, finally a  move on

and immediately he goes, full, outside off, he drags it from there, goes to beat midwicket, and gives Bopara a sitter. Chanderpaul had to work hard for his runs, but not enough intent in his innings, one feels
back of a length, played to midwicket for one
slower bouncer, Ramdin is early into the pull, and doesn't get enough power into this one
goes full, wide, too wide
full and wide, flashes, ends up slicing it over point
full and wide again, driven to extra cover for one
full and wide is his plan, but this one is too wide again
full and wide he stays, Ramdin opens the face of the bat, and gets two square of third man
game, set, match, slower bouncer, cuts in, Ramdin cuts hard, gets a thick edge, Prior takes it one-handed
full, straight, driven down the ground, off the mark
wide outside off, gets onto the front foot, and chops it down for one
short, onto the pads, and turned away towards fine leg
short, into the body, pulls it to fine leg
short again, into the chest, plays with the bottom hand off the bat, gets one towards fine leg
bouncer again, and pulled down to fine leg
slower ball, on the pads, and helped away fine of deep fine leg for four
short, chest high again, drops it into the on side and gets one, 200 up, joy to the world
full, outside off, drives it down to mid-on for one
short and wide, goes bor the cuts, gets bottom edge for one
short and wide again, pushed off the front foot, to sweeper-cover
excellent yorker, on off stump, dug out, back to the bowler
good pull shot, short, on off stump, gets across and pulls it over midwicket
and he pulls again, from outside off, and clears mid-on easily, two good purposeful shot

bowls a big wide down the leg side, and hang on, a bizarre dismissal, Pollard wants one on a fumble, but is sent back by Taylor, Pollard dives in to make it in, but when the hand hits the ground, the bat goes up in the air, and immediately then Prior's throw hits the stumps
digs it in short, into the pads, gets one leg-bye
pulls again, bouncer into his face, doesn't connect properly but this doesn't carry to deep backward square
fuller this time, shouts for lbw, but the angle is taking the ball down the leg side
short, angling in, Benn pulls but the ball passes under his bat
goes for the yorker, third man in the circle, Benn gets a thick edge for four
slower offcutter, deceives Benn on the pull
four from inside edge, full outside off, and fine leg's up
goes for the slog, gets a thick inside edge back to the bowler
steps out, gets a yorker, played back to the bowler
slower ball, outside off, and runs it down to third man
bouncer, and he is way too late into the pull

another run-out, good length, gets a thick edge towards point, Strauss fields, looks up and sees a mid-pitch confusion and Taylor has to hurry back towards the none-striker's end, the throw is good, on the bounce and he is found short. Lots of yesses and nos in this one
back of a length, outside off, and chopped towards point for one, and Strauss's yorker of a throw goes through Prior for an overthrow
short, goes for the big heave, gets a top edge that lands between point and third man
slower ball, on a length, and played back to the bowler
Benn gets a six now, hooks it from in front of his face, gets a top edge that sails over deep backward square
looks to make room, Broad follows him, and goes through a defensive prod
short, stays low, pulled towards deep backward square
darts a quick one into the pads, defended back to the bowler
flights this one well, Benn looks to turn it to leg, gets a leading edge for one to point
flat again, on the stumps, and defended back to Swann
quicker again, outside off, full, and beats Rampaul's drive
throws it up generously, Rampaul waits for it, is yorked, but gets one to cover
steps out, and wafts it across the line, gets one for his troubles
good flat-batted pull, short, into his body, not much pace into it, and he clears midwicket easily
full, outside off, driven off the back foot to cover for one
now Rampaul pulls for four, tries to bounce, and he has enough time to rock back and pull, in front of square
full, angling in, played down to long-on
that's better, a yorker outside off, Benn plays inside the line
fulltoss, hit straight to cover
good loft over the bowler's head, steps out, gets to the pitch off it and clears his arms
slogs it along the ground for one to deep midwicket
goes for the reverse-sweep, misses, his pads save him
steps out and slogs, gets one
tries one shot too many, makes room, looks to go inside out out, Swann fires it straight, gets the middle stump
tosses it up wide outside off, Edwards drives, misses completely
slower offcutter, and he drops it into covers and takes one
goes for the full and straight one, it's a low fulltoss, and he gets a single down the ground, no words or looks exchanged
on the pads, Benn turns it to between deep backward square and deep midwicket
back of a length, on the pads, and he gets two into the leg side
slower bouncer, he is too early into the pull, the ball comes 10 minutes later and hits him in the stomach
this is normal pace, Benn steps out, and pulls it to deep midwicket boundary
fulltoss on the pads, he plays it down to long-on
full, outside off, and driven to sweeper-cover
slower ball, Edwards plays it with an open face towards point
dropped, even Strauss wants one final go between Anderson and Edwards, Edwards gives it his all, lobs it towards extra cover, Strauss goes one-handed over his head and drops
low fulltoss, driven to extra cover for one
full, on the middle stump, driven to extra cover
fulltoss, played down the ground
yorker outside off, plays over it
low fulltoss, driven down to long-off, still no visual animosity
yorker, middle stump, bowled, thanks for coming West Indies. But maybe not, the way they have played through both the Test and ODI series
